Class
Description
BuildConstants
Automatically generated file containing build version information.
CANDeviceDetails
Represents a CAN device with identifying details such as ID, bus name, manufacturer, and subsystem.
CANDeviceDetails.Manufacturer
Enum representing the manufacturer of the CAN device.
MotorBase
Represents a general-purpose base class for motor controllers, handling logging, alerting, and access to closed-loop control methods.
MotorBuilder
A builder class for configuring and generating a TalonFXConfiguration for CTRE TalonFX motor controllers.
MotorBuilder.FeedbackSensorType
Type of feedback sensor used for closed-loop control.
MotorBuilder.RequestType
Type of control used for this motor.
MotorIO
MotorIO defines a hardware abstraction interface for motor input-output operations.
MotorIO.MotorIOInputs
Container class for motor telemetry and status inputs.
MotorIOSim
Simulated implementation of the MotorIO interface.
MotorIOTalonFX
Hardware I/O implementation for the CTRE TalonFX motor using the Phoenix 6 API.
MotorRequest
Interface for defining motor control request behaviors.
MotorStateMachine
A simple state machine for representing and managing the operational state of a motor.
MotorStateMachine.MotorState
Enumeration of possible motor operational states.
PhoenixUtil
Phoenix utility too attempt to apply settings a given number of times.
PositionControl
Position control strategy for a motor using either voltage-based or FOC-based closed-loop control.
SoftwareLimits
Represents a software-enforced limit that can be enabled or disabled.
VelocityControl
Class representing a velocity control request for motor controllers.
